@startuml

start

:Blobless clone of the Backstage repository;
note right
Clones only commit and tree objects,
avoiding heavy blob downloads.
This enables lightweight analysis
of Git history.
end note

:01_extract_commits.py;
note right
Extracts one row for each pair:
(commit, modified file) from git log.
end note

:02_filter_commits.py;
note right
Removes methodological noise:
- merge commits
- bots
- oversized commits
- non-code files
- .changeset/*
end note

fork
  :03_cochange_analysis.py;
  note right
  Computes logical coupling:
  files changed together in the same commits.

  Metrics:
  - support
  - confidence
  - jaccard
  end note
fork again
  :04_author_coupling.py;
  note right
  Computes socio-technical coupling:
  files related because they are modified
  by the same authors.

  Metrics:
  - jaccard_authors
  - cosine_authors
  end note
end fork

:05_build_graph.py;
note right
Combines co-change and author coupling
into a weighted graph.

Formula:
w = 0.7 * jaccard_cochange
  + 0.3 * cosine_authors

Then applies Louvain algorithm
to detect communities.
end note

:07_c4_diagram.py;
note right
Aggregates files at package level
and generates a readable C4 view.

Mapping:
- Container = package
- System_Boundary = Louvain community
- Rel_Neighbor = coupling between packages
end note

stop

@enduml